## Allotment of Equity Shares

The Equity Shares shall be allotted within a period of three Working Days from the Bid/Issue Closing Date. The Allotment Advice shall be dispatched within a period of five Working Days from the Bid/Issue Closing Date. The Allottee shall be intimated of the Allotment of Equity Shares through the Allotment Advice. The Allotment Advice shall be sent to the Allottee at the address as mentioned in the Bid cum Application Form.

In case of over-subscription, the Allotment shall be made on a pro-rata basis. In case of under-subscription, the Allotment shall be made to the extent of the subscription received.

The Allotment Advice shall contain the following details:

- Name of the Allottee;
- Number of Equity Shares allotted;
- Amount paid on application;
- Amount payable on allotment;
- Amount refunded, if any;
- Name of the Bank Account in which the refund amount has been credited;
- Name of the Depository Participant and the DP ID and Client ID of the Allottee; and
- Such other details as may be prescribed by SEBI.

The Allottee shall be responsible for ensuring that the details mentioned in the Bid cum Application Form are correct. In case of any discrepancy, the Allottee shall intimate the same to the Registrar to the Issue within three Working Days from the date of receipt of the Allotment Advice.

## Refund of Application Money

In case of over-subscription, the excess application money shall be refunded to the Allottee within a period of fifteen Working Days from the Bid/Issue Closing Date. In case of under-subscription, the entire application money shall be refunded to the Allottee within a period of fifteen Working Days from the Bid/Issue Closing Date.

The refund amount shall be credited to the Bank Account specified by the Allottee in the Bid cum Application Form. In case the Bank Account specified by the Allottee is not valid or is closed, the refund amount shall be credited to the Bank Account of the Allottee as per the records maintained by the Registrar to the Issue.

## Listing of Equity Shares

The Equity Shares shall be listed on the Bombay Stock Exchange Limited and the National Stock Exchange of India Limited within a period of thirty Working Days from the Bid/Issue Closing Date.

## Trading of Equity Shares

The Equity Shares shall be traded in dematerialised form only. The Equity Shares shall be traded in multiples of one Equity Share.

## Lock-in Period

There shall be no lock-in period for the Equity Shares issued in this Issue.

## Use of Proceeds

The net proceeds of the Issue shall be utilised for the purposes mentioned in the “Objects of the Issue” section of this Draft Red Herring Prospectus.

## Risk Factors

Investors are advised to read the “Risk Factors” section of this Draft Red Herring Prospectus carefully before investing in the Equity Shares.

